      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/12545</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I would suggest you have a look at my&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://github.com/gregorwolf/mtxs-bookshop" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://github.com/gregorwolf/mtxs-bookshop&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;example. There I use the&amp;nbsp;service: build-workzone-standard with&amp;nbsp;service-plan: standard. That way you have a launchpad experience directly after subscription and you don't need to deploy the UI5 apps to the subscriber subaccount in an extra step. Right now I'm researching in the branch&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://github.com/gregorwolf/mtxs-bookshop/tree/flp-content-exposure" target="_self" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;flp-content-exposure&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;if I could provide the same content that S/4HANA Cloud or also the BTP ABAP environment provide to allow the integration directly in Build Work Zone of the Client as a content provider.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
